President Donald J. Trump has authorized an increase in federal funding for debris removal and emergency protective measures in the state of Texas following Hurricane Harvey. The increase in funding includes a 90 percent federal cost share for debris removal and a 100 percent federal funding for emergency protective measures for the first 30 days, and then a 90 percent federal cost share thereafter. The funding is available as part of the major disaster declaration issued for Texas on August 25, 2017. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.